resource.chars: 7 meirt 1695
London Richard Southeel
Sence my last to you on 14 cur non from you, so referre
you to the same & desire the northrens be added 2 to N10 ƒ
4 p 6 a yd or there about raw & where as these & other goods to
be ordered for the futture could be shipped aboard such vessels
as I could be interessed with goods shipt by M Kent so would
desire you to ensure tall what you shall send mee chargeing the
actt with provision & insurance 3½ pc from londen & 4½
from hull, which of you accept of please to advise mee that
I send you my order accordingley, I suppose when the hurrey for
the militia in kersies & bayes cottons & a be over that hem
sort of goods will be plentier & att the old rate of last yeare
of which your advise whilst I rest
ugg CCoots
hem beaut 4 & 6 deser & gevraght wegens convo
van london, een correspondenelt Deamherpien
oft goed ter wagen coen comen van dapiker an
Cortrijck de weduwe Causse
Ick hebbe op 22 feb laestleden staelen van swerte lakens
aen ue gesonden ick hadde verwaght ue eenige daer van soudt
hebben ontboden ni hope ick ue sone haest hier te sien
voorders chchryve desen om ue te laeten weten dat die van
duynaescken een schip hebben opgebrogh comende van hull
naer Rotterdam gelaeden met baeyen kersijn & noerts lakens
& alsoo ick daer by eenighsins ben geintresseert & dat ick
geloove die goederen daer haest sullen vercoght worde
soo is mijne vraege ofte men die goederen tot brugge magh
brengen, ofte de spaense het incomen gedoogen & ofte ue
see mons Jan Capt denvaerts soude willen gaen
omden in coop te doen, middelertijt wenschte wel ue geliefte
naer duynckerken te laeten in formeren, wanneer die
goederen vercoght sullen worden, verwaghte hier over
ue antwoort & naer groetenisse blyv
londen Walt & will kent
I refeire you to my last of 17 cur wher I remitted
£340: in a bill of which the seconds are accepted
in handes of david de bary so procure them or the needfull
now have before mee yours of p ditto wee have no news
of the ships from london I doubt the convoy was
no readdy or would not come to margett road for ito
saile to duyn without convoy is to loose all good present
them Lam att aloss by having not the goods wanting
gett seeing you say the honth of april will be the best
time for buying, so buy no bayes nor kessies till you see
good times a then buy 100 of 30 yd, itt zeems the dutsch
will putt an imbarge till their fleet be out, so I doubt if soon
convoj will be given for hull so lett good measures betaken
for buying goods att leeds, yett make haste for 12 northrens to
be sent up to london for ostend, & where as there is avere good
convoj with you att present for Rott so send the 10 northrens
that way, which you say to send acctt of p first, that is provide
they can come with this convoy as I hope send by the same
5 pack whites EE yea keep the crest for ostend for which place
I hope soorn an lother convoy shall present & there with my orders
compleared & that buying for clotheng you soldiess be over by
this time, which is the needfull ats present from lett parti
enlarly be observed that onee & for all the northrens be noted
witha p of thrade were they are so to gother because wee
sell must the halves & onles wee see that ss will losse
after wards
21 meirt
Amst geerd rover
In antwort aende ue van 17 & 18 deser hpe de 2 packe
over ter goude gexxpedieert volgens het seggen vande
benstleyden, voorgaende donderdagh van daer syn vertrocke
& deselve heden ofte morgen hier sullen arriveren tis well
dat ue het pack N1 aen samuel forrin hadt gelevers
ick bidde ue my tijdelijck te adviseren soo haest convoy naer
ull wort verleend ofte soo wanneer de seevaert sonde
verboden worden tot taldertyt toe de oorloalschepen
in dae syn sulckx oock te laeten weten om mes uier naer
advenant te nemen, ick wenschte wel eerst ue opinie hadde
gehadt eer ick die st £300 op londen hadt afgegeven
n'ingesloten seynde an geaccepteerde brief van ƒ£37:10
ten laste vander laenen & fendi in Amst heden vervalle
welcke weirde gelieft in te voorderen & als ue sal dunckende
will op laeghst te wesen £200 op londen af te geven in
2 verscheyde frieven verhopen dat de geramitteerde £140:- adde
by arens van denirs sullen worden voldaen, t welck ick geirne
sal verstaen, hope sy de uytterste desden valdagh niet sulle
afwaghten, wat voor balt verneme geirne & naer groetenisse
blijven one convoy van londen naer brugge p 7 deser van daer vertrocken
kan door contrarie wint niet op schieten gelieft te laeten ussureren in
tschip van magnus mason genaempt de voorsightigheyt £150:- soo
